Enable latex equations:

You need to enable latex in the source/conf.py file first by adding this line:

myst_enable_extensions = ["dollarmath", "amsmath"]

Then you can write some latex:

\[\begin{split} \begin{eqnarray} y & = & ax^2 + bx + c \\ f(x) & = & x^2 + 2xy + y^2 \end{eqnarray} \end{split}\]

For more infos, and more extensions, see this page: https://myst-parser.readthedocs.io/en/latest/syntax/optional.html .
